oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Jim York From Music City U. S. A.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Offset printing; York, Jim;
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white negatives taped to and framed by a masking sheet advertising Jim York, from Music City USA., available through Gerald Pinkelton Attractions. The negative features a head and shoulders portrait of Jim York and a full length group portrait featuring Jim York with Garrett Sullivan, the Jordanaires, Billy Gray, Junior Husky, Pig Robinson, Buddy Harmon, Lloyd Green, and Leon Rhodes at RCA Studio in Nashville during York's recording sessions. The negative would have been used to create a corresponding printing plate.
